DOM (Document Object Modeling)
--> is the interface between our javascript and HTML/CSS

-->The broweser turns every HTML tags into a javascript object can manapulate. 
-->Everything is stored inside the Document Object.

DOM Selector
============
document.getElementById()
document.getElementByClassName()
document.getElementByTagName()
document.querySelector("#myDiv")

to fix the problem in script tag 
<script src="./index.html"></script>

==> Defer
<script defer src="./index.html"></script>

==>Async
<script async src="./index.html"></script>

Global Object
Window->document->location->navigator->screen->history



getElementsByClassName() returns a live HTMLCollection.
getElementsByTagName() returns a live HTMLCollection.
getElementsByName() returns a live NodeList.
querySelectorAll() returns a static NodeList.


==> "this" keyword in eventHandler invocke the html element


